    "# Iteration 2 — Per-column top analysis (ruled out as discriminator)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal.** Iteration 1 found that `below_near` (intensity 10–50 µm under the candidate surface z) separates the real pia from the AF-contaminated v21 surface on 755252.  Before designing a full quality metric, we check whether the signal is also present at the per-column-top level so we could filter individual tops during Stage 3 instead of rescoring whole surfaces.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Procedure.**  For each subject, replicate v2.1 Stage 2 (anchor) and Stage 3 (per-column tops in the ±150 µm band around the anchor). Label each top as `pia` (|z_top − N22(x,y)| ≤ 25 µm) or `AF` (otherwise) and measure `below_near` in the subsampled combined volume.  Data: `data/iter02_tops.csv`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Result.**  Per-top `below_near` does **not** separate AF tops from pia tops: both are bright immediately below (AF because the probed slab falls inside the AF body; pia because the slab falls in real tissue).  The iter-1 signal is specific to the *surface z*, which on 755252 sits in the **gap** between AF bottom and the real pia onset.  That gap is narrow and individual column tops usually don't land inside it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Conclusion: move to a surface-level quality score (iter 3)."
   ]
  },
