    "## Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Across all subjects, tops in the `[−50, −10]` bin (the few stage-3 survivors that sit above N22 — likely AF tops) have `below_near` values indistinguishable from tops at pia or deep tissue.  The signal we saw in iter-1 was specific to evaluating features **at the fitted surface z**, because the fitted surface on 755252 ends up in the *gap* between AF bottom and real pia onset — a location where individual column tops rarely sit.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Therefore we shift strategy**: rather than filtering individual tops during Stage 3, we'll design a **surface-level quality score** in iteration 3 and use it to auto-select among candidate surfaces (different channel subsets or fit parameters)."
   ]
